1 About

1.1 Tables of fine-mapping results

Columns in tables of fine-mapping results (presented below for each locus):

  • zscore: Z-score of single-SNP association test;
  • pval: the p-value of single-SNP association test;
  • snp_prob: the posterior probability of SNP to be causal (estimated by FINEMAP in the region);
  • snp_log10bf: the associated Bayes Factor (log 10 base);
  • prop_zscore: the ratio between zscore and the best zscore;
  • prop_snp_prob: the ratio between snp_prob and the best snp_prob.

1.2 Overlapping with smoking-dependent methylation QTLs

Article Genetically contextual effects of smoking on genome wide DNA methylation, 2017, Am J Med Genet B Neuropsychiatr Genet.

Data description

  • 2,567 inidviduals (of the 5,125 inidividuals in total) have the methylation data measured in blood
  • (clean) 484,241 CpG methylation sites measured by the Illumina HumanMethylation450 BeadChip
  • (clean) 403,192 SNPs

Results reported in the article:

Analysis Tests Significant Proprotion BF Threshold
Smoking effects on probe 484,125 525 0.108% 1e-7
Interaction SNPxSmoking cis-mQTL 126,369,511 827 0.0065% 3.96e-10
Interaction SNPxSmoking trans-mQTL 195,068,554,297 448,242 0.00023% 2.60e-13
  • 1M window for cis-effects. Otherwise, trans-effects.
  • The outcome is methylation probes (CpG islands).

Limitations:

  • The individuals are elderly individuals of European ancestry.
  • The methylation arrays is not state-of-the art.

1.2.1 Tables of methylation annotations

We mined the significant QTLs based on several filters (the first column in the tables below):

  • smk_by_meth: interaction signal overlapped with the locus region based on CpG positions;
  • cis_by_meth: interaction cis-mQTL overlapped with the locus region based on CpG positions;
  • cis_by_snp: interaction cis-mQTL overlapped with the locus region based on SNP positions;
  • trans_by_meth: interaction trans-mQTL overlapped with the locus region based on CpG positions;
  • trans_by_snp: interaction trans-mQTL overlapped with the locus region based on SNP positions;
